Year	new month	Source	Location	Event		
1990	8/1/1998	Wikipedia	National	 Clinton-Lewinsky scandal: President Clinton is accused of having a sexual relationship with 22-year-old White House intern Monica Lewinsky. This leads to the impeachment of Clinton later in the year by the U.S. House of Representatives. Clinton is acquitted of all impeachment charges of perjury and obstruction of justice in a 21-day Senate trial.		
1999	3/1/1999	Wikipedia	National	" The Dow Jones Industrial Average closes above the 10,000 mark for the first time, at 10,006.78."		
1999	4/1/1999	Wikipedia	Colorado	" Teenage students Eric Harris and Dylan Klebold murder 13 other students and teachers at Columbine High School, sparking an international debate on gun control and bullying."		
1999	5/1/1999	Wikipedia	Oklahoma	 A violent tornado outbreak in Oklahoma kills 50 people and becomes the first to produce a tornado that causes $1 billion in damage.		
1999	10/1/1999	Wikipedia	Massachusetts	" The first officer deliberately crashes EgyptAir Flight 990 south of Nantucket, Massachusetts, killing 217."		
1999	12/1/1999	Wikipedia	National	" Along with the rest of the world, the U.S. prepares for the possible effects of the Y2K bug in computers, which was feared to cause computers to become inoperable and wreak havoc. The problem isn't as large as theorized, preparations are successful, and disaster is averted."		
2000	10/1/2000	Wikipedia	National	" The Arleigh Burke-class destroyer, the USS Cole (DDG-76) is bombed in Yemeni waters, killing seventeen U.S. Navy sailors."		
2000	11/1/2000	Wikipedia	National	" U.S. presidential election, 2000: Initial result inconclusive and the result in Florida is disputed. George W. Bush is certified president after a Supreme Court ruling. Vice President Al Gore wins the nationwide popular vote but loses the electoral college."		
2001	1/1/2001	Wikipedia	National	" George W. Bush becomes the 43rd President, Dick Cheney becomes Vice President."		
2001	1/1/2001	Wikipedia	National	 Democrats gains narrow control of Senate after James Jeffords defects from the Republican Party.		
2001	12/1/2001	Wikipedia	National	 No Child Left Behind Act education reform bill passed.		
2001	6/1/2001	Wikipedia	National	 Economic Growth and Tax Relief Reconciliation Act of 2001 institutes large tax cuts.		
2001	9/1/2001	Wikipedia	National	" September 11 attacks; 19 terrorists hijack four planes and crash them into the World Trade Center, the Pentagon, and a field in Shanksville, Pennsylvania killing nearly 3,000 people and injuring over 6,000. All civilian air traffic is suspended for three days, the first time an unplanned suspension had occurred in U.S. history."		
2001	9/1/2001	Wikipedia	National	 Congress passes an emergency bailout package for the airline industry as a result of the attacks		
2001	9/1/2001	Wikipedia	National	 Anthrax attacks kill 5 and infect a further 17 through the U.S. Mail system.		
2001	10/1/2001	Wikipedia	National	 The United States launches the invasion of Afghanistan marking the start of Operation Enduring Freedom.		
2001	10/1/2001	Wikipedia	National	" Patriot Act, increasing law enforcement agencies' ability to conduct searches in cases of suspected terrorism. Agencies were enforced."		
2001	11/1/2001	Wikipedia	New York	" American Airlines Flight 587 crashes in Queens, New York, killing 265."		
2002	11/1/2002	Wikipedia	National	 The Department of Homeland Security is created in the wake of the September 11 attacks.		
2002	6/1/2002	Wikipedia	National	 The United States withdraws from Anti-Ballistic Missile Treaty.		
2002	10/1/2002	Wikipedia	Washington DC	 10 people are killed and 3 are injured in the Beltway sniper attacks around the Washington D.C. area.		
2003	1/1/2003	Wikipedia	National	 Republicans retake narrow control of the Senate following 2002 elections.		
2003	2/1/2003	Wikipedia	National	" Space Shuttle Columbia disintegrates upon re-entry to the Earth's atmosphere, killing all seven astronauts and resulting in a 29-month suspension of the Space Shuttle program."		
2003	2/1/2003	Wikipedia	Illinois	E2 nightclub stampede		
2003	3/1/2003	Wikipedia	National	" The United States, United Kingdom, Australia and Poland invades Iraq marking the start of Operation Iraqi Freedom."		
2003	3/1/2003	Wikipedia	National	 U.S. forces continue fighting an insurgency in Iraq while helping the Iraqis build a new army of their own and develop a democratic form of government		
2003	12/1/2003	Wikipedia	National	" In Iraq, deposed Iraqi president Saddam Hussein is captured by U.S. special forces."		
2004	2/1/2004	Wikipedia	National	 The social networking website Facebook is launched.		
2004	5/1/2004	Wikipedia	Massachusetts	 Massachusetts becomes the first state to legalize same-sex marriage in compliance with a ruling from the state's Supreme Court ruling in Goodridge v. Department of Public Health		
2004	6/1/2004	Wikipedia	National	 Former U.S. President Ronald Reagan dies from complications resulting from Alzheimer's Disease. He lies in state at the U.S. Capitol building before being interred.		
2004	9/1/2004	thoughtco	National	Violent Crime Control and Law Enforcement Act of 1994 banning the sale of 19 types of military-style assault weapons to expire.		
2004	11/1/2004	Wikipedia	National	" George W. Bush is re-elected president, Dick Cheney is re-elected vice president."		
2004	12/1/2004	thoughtco	Massachusetts	Massachusetts becomes the first state to implement an electronic instant gun buyer background check system with fingerprint scanning for gun licenses and gun purchases.		
2005	1/1/2005	Wikipedia	National	 President Bush and Vice President Cheney begin their second terms		
2005	1/1/2005	thoughtco	California	"California bans the manufacture, sale, distribution or import of the powerful .50-caliber BMG, or Browning machine gun rifle."		
2005	9/1/2005	Wikipedia	Louisiana	" Hurricane Katrina devastates the Louisiana, Mississippi, and Alabama coastlines killing at least 1,836 people and causing $81 billion in damage, making it the costliest natural disaster in U.S. history. Weeks later, Hurricane Rita causes $10 billion damage along the Louisiana and Texas coastlines. In October, Hurricane Wilma kills 35 and causes $20 billion in damage in Florida."		
2005	10/1/2005	thoughtco	National	President Bush signs the Protection of Lawful Commerce in Arms Act limiting the ability of victims of crimes in which guns were used to sue firearms manufacturers and dealers. The law includes an amendment requiring all new guns to come with trigger locks.		
2006	1/1/2006	Wikipedia	National	" The Democratic Party retakes control of both houses of Congress, and gains a majority of state governorships (28-22)."		
2007	1/1/2007	Wikipedia	National	 Democrat Nancy Pelosi becomes the first female Speaker of the U.S. House of Representatives		
2007	1/1/2007	Wikipedia	National	" George W. Bush orders a troop surge which substantially increases the number of U.S. troops in Iraq and ultimately leads to reductions in casualties and major victories for coalition and Iraqi forces, against the insurgency."		
2007	4/1/2007	Wikipedia	Virginia	 A South Korean student shoots and kills 32 other students and professors in the Virginia Tech massacre before killing himself. It stands as the worst mass shooting in U.S. history until 2016 and spurs a series of debates on gun control and journalism ethics.		
2007	8/1/2007	Wikipedia	Minnesota	" The I-35W Mississippi River bridge in Minneapolis, Minnesota collapses, killing 13 people. The bridge collapse brings to national attention the need to rehabilitate the aging U.S. infrastructure system."		
2007	12/1/2007	Wikipedia	National	 The late-2000s recession officially begins in December.		
2008	1/1/2008	thoughtco	National	"President Bush signs the National Instant Criminal Background Check Improvement Act requiring gun-buyer background checks to screen for legally declared mentally ill individuals, who are ineligible to buy firearms."		
2008	2/1/2008	Wikipedia	Arkansas	" The Super Tuesday tornado outbreak kills over 60 people and produces $1 billion in damage across Arkansas, Kentucky, Tennessee, and Alabama."		
2008	2/1/2008	Wikipedia	Illinois	" A student kills five, injures 21, and then kills himself in the Northern Illinois University shooting. After this incident, calls are made for more focus on mental health services and interest grows substantially in the group Students for Concealed Carry on Campus."		
2008	6/1/2008	thoughtco	Washington DC	"District of Columbia v. Heller, the U.S. Supreme Court ruled that the Second Amendment affirmed the rights of individuals to own firearms. The ruling also overturns a 32-year-old ban on the sale or possession of handguns in the District of Columbia."		
2008	9/1/2008	Wikipedia	Texas	" Hurricane Ike kills 100 people along the Texas coast, produces $31 billion in damage, and contributes to rising oil prices."		
2008	7/1/2008	Wikipedia	National	 U.S. oil prices hit a record $147 per barrel in the wake of	among other factors	international tensions and the falling U.S. dollar vs. the Euro.
2008	9/1/2008	Wikipedia	National	" A global financial crisis begins as the stock market crashes. In response, U.S. President George W. Bush signs the revised Emergency Economic Stabilization Act into law to create a 700 billion dollar Treasury fund to purchase failing bank assets."		
2008	11/1/2008	Wikipedia	National	" U.S. presidential election, 2008: Barack Obama is elected president, and Joe Biden vice president."		
